sudokuGame

Class Primitive

  • java.lang.Object
    • sudokuGame.TerminalOrPrimitive
      • sudokuGame.Primitive
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Primitive
extends TerminalOrPrimitive
    Primitive class is representing the the primitive operating (primitive node) in our Tree-based Genetic Programing. And we use this class as a generic T value in the Node class. The primitive set that we support is : +, -, *, /, %, Max, Min, But the list can be extended.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Abedalrhman Nsasra
    See Also:
    Node, TerminalOrPrimitive, Terminal, Genetic Programming

      • run

        double run(int row,
           int col,
           int key,
           int[][] board,
           java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Double>[][] gradeBoard)
        Call run method on the left and right children in recursive way, and then do the operation (+, -, *, /, %, Max, Min) on the result of the grade child and the right child, notice that all the calls are recursive on the left child and the right child. Notice: that all the operations are binary operation, because our Tree-based Genetic Programing is binary.
        Specified by:
        run in class TerminalOrPrimitive
        Parameters:
        row - The index of the row in the Sudoku board.
        col - The index of the column in the Sudoku board.
        key - One of the options (number 1-9) that can be inserted in [row,col] in the board without conflict.
        board - Reference to the Sudoku board matrix with size 9x9, we don't copy the board it's just a reference.
        gradeBoard - Reference to matrix of hash tables that represent in every index in the matrix which numbers can be inserted without conflict as a keys in the hash table and grade as a value for every key that represent how good this option as solution, we choose smaller grade is better but you could choose larger is better, it will not change the solution.
        Returns:
        a grade that represent how much good the key parameter as solution in [row,col] index in Sudoku board, we have determined smaller is a better grade.
        See Also:
        Terminal.run(int, int, int, int[][], Hashtable[][]), run(int, int, int, int[][], Hashtable[][])
